{"title_page": "Anuradha Lohia", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Anuradha Lohia\n| image = \n| alt = \n| caption = Prof. Anuradha Lohia\n| birth_date = \n| birth_place = \n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| residence = {{ublist |[[India]]}}\n| nationality = [[Indian people|Indian]]\n| fields = \n| workplaces = [[Bose Institute]], [[Presidency University, Kolkata|Presidency University]]\n| alma_mater = {{ublist | [[Presidency College, Kolkata|Presidency College]]<br>([[University of Calcutta]]) | [[Rajabazar Science College]]<br/>([[University of Calcutta]]) | [[Indian Institute of Chemical Biology]]}}\n| office = 3rd Vice-Chancellor of [[Presidency University, Kolkata|Presidency University]]\n| governor = [[M.K. Narayanan]]<br>[[Keshari Nath Tripathi]]<br>[[Jagdeep Dhankhar]]\n| term_start = 2 May 2014\n| predecessor = [[Malabika Sarkar]]\n| doctoral_advisor = \n| doctoral_students = \n\n| awards = \n| native_name_lang = \u0985\u09a8\u09c1\u09b0\u09be\u09a7\u09be \u09b2\u09cb\u09b9\u09bf\u09af\u09bc\u09be\n| chancellor = [[Governor of West Bengal]]\n}}\n''' Anuradha Lohia ''' ({{Nee}} '''Fatehpuria''')   is an Indian molecular [[parasitologist]] who works in [[infectious disease]]. <ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.presiuniv.ac.in/web/staff.php?staffid=185 | title=Anuradha Lohia Vice Chancellor | publisher=[[Presidency University, Kolkata]] | accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://boseinst.ernet.in/anuradha/ | title=Anuradha Lohia | publisher=[[Bose Institute]] | accessdate=13 July 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160722121743/http://www.boseinst.ernet.in/anuradha/ | archive-date=22 July 2016 | url-status=dead }}</ref> She is currently the Vice Chancellor of the [[Presidency University, Kolkata|Presidency University]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1140427/jsp/bengal/story_18283552.jsp#.V4WbyjWaaUk | title=Lohia selected as Presidency VC | publisher=[[The Telegraph (Calcutta)]] | date=27 April 2014 | accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2015-08-22/news/65739778_1_convocation-ceremony-students-union-vc | title=Presidency University VC Anuradha Lohia under gherao since last evening | publisher=[[The Economic Times]] | date=22 August 2015 | accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://indianexpress.com/article/cities/kolkata/presidency-university-stalemate-students-vacate-v-c-anuradha-lohias-chambers-panel-set-up-to-hear-them-out/ | title=Presidency University stalemate: Students vacate V-C Anuradha Lohia\u2019s chambers, panel set up to hear them out | publisher=[[Indian Express]] | date=26 August 2015 | accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/kolkata/Happy-to-feature-on-Presidency-Universitys-vice-chancellor-probable-list-Lohia/articleshow/34169174.cms | title=Happy to feature on Presidency University's vice chancellor probable list: Lohia | publisher=[[Times of India]] | work=Jhimli Mukherjee Pandey | date=25 April 2014 | accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref> She was earlier the Chairperson of Department of Biochemistry in the [[Bose Institute]] in [[Kolkata]]. She was Chairperson of an Indo-British Wellcome Trust/ DBT India Alliance, an organization to promote medical research in India.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://indiabioscience.org/columns/conversations/ten-women-ten-questions-anuradha-lohia | title=Ten women, ten questions: Anuradha Lohia | publisher=indiabioscience.org | date=17 July 2015 | accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Education and career==\nShe was a student of Modern High School for Girls in [[Calcutta]]. She did a B.Sc. in Physiology from [[Presidency College, Kolkata|Presidency College]] in [[Calcutta University]] and M.Sc. in Physiology from [[Rajabazar Science College]], [[Calcutta University]] and later did her doctorate in [[Vibrio cholerae]] from the [[Indian Institute of Chemical Biology]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Anuradha Lohia,|url=http://www.streeshakti.com/Anuradha-Lohia.aspx|publisher=StreeShakti|accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref> She was visiting scientist in various universities in the World. She did her Postdoctoral research in New York University Medical Centre. She was elected a fellow of the [[Indian Academy of Sciences]]. She was also awarded the Stree Shakti award and the UNESCO Molecular and Cell Biology network grant.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-aca}}\n{{s-bef|before = [[Malabika Sarkar]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title = [[Presidency University, Kolkata|Vice-Chancellor of Presidency University, Kolkata]]|years = since 2014}}\n{{s-aft|after= incumbent}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lohia, Anuradha}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Indian parasitologists]]\n[[Category:Indian women biologists]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian biologists]]\n[[Category:University of Calcutta alumni]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Women parasitologists]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Anuradha Lohia\n| image = \n| alt = \n| caption = Prof. Anuradha Lohia\n| birth_date = \n| birth_place = \n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| residence = {{ublist |[[India]]}}\n| nationality = [[Indian people|Indian]]\n| fields = \n| workplaces = [[Bose Institute]], [[Presidency University, Kolkata|Presidency University]]\n| alma_mater = {{ublist | [[Presidency College]]<br>([[University of Calcutta]]) | [[Rajabazar Science College]]<br/>([[University of Calcutta]]) | [[Indian Institute of Chemical Biology]]}}\n| office = 3rd Vice-Chancellor of [[Presidency University, Kolkata|Presidency University]]\n| governor = [[M.K. Narayanan]]<br>[[Keshari Nath Tripathi]]<br>[[Jagdeep Dhankhar]]\n| term_start = 2 May 2014\n| predecessor = [[Malabika Sarkar]]\n| doctoral_advisor = \n| doctoral_students = \n\n| awards = \n| native_name_lang = \u0985\u09a8\u09c1\u09b0\u09be\u09a7\u09be \u09b2\u09cb\u09b9\u09bf\u09af\u09bc\u09be\n| chancellor = [[Governor of West Bengal]]\n}}\n''' Anuradha Lohia ''' ({{Nee}} '''Fatehpuria''')   is an Indian molecular [[parasitologist]] who works in [[infectious disease]]. <ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.presiuniv.ac.in/web/staff.php?staffid=185 | title=Anuradha Lohia Vice Chancellor | publisher=[[Presidency University, Kolkata]] | accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://boseinst.ernet.in/anuradha/ | title=Anuradha Lohia | publisher=[[Bose Institute]] | accessdate=13 July 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160722121743/http://www.boseinst.ernet.in/anuradha/ | archive-date=22 July 2016 | url-status=dead }}</ref> She is currently the Vice Chancellor of the [[Presidency University, Kolkata|Presidency University]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1140427/jsp/bengal/story_18283552.jsp#.V4WbyjWaaUk | title=Lohia selected as Presidency VC | publisher=[[The Telegraph (Calcutta)]] | date=27 April 2014 | accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2015-08-22/news/65739778_1_convocation-ceremony-students-union-vc | title=Presidency University VC Anuradha Lohia under gherao since last evening | publisher=[[The Economic Times]] | date=22 August 2015 | accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://indianexpress.com/article/cities/kolkata/presidency-university-stalemate-students-vacate-v-c-anuradha-lohias-chambers-panel-set-up-to-hear-them-out/ | title=Presidency University stalemate: Students vacate V-C Anuradha Lohia\u2019s chambers, panel set up to hear them out | publisher=[[Indian Express]] | date=26 August 2015 | accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/kolkata/Happy-to-feature-on-Presidency-Universitys-vice-chancellor-probable-list-Lohia/articleshow/34169174.cms | title=Happy to feature on Presidency University's vice chancellor probable list: Lohia | publisher=[[Times of India]] | work=Jhimli Mukherjee Pandey | date=25 April 2014 | accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref> She was earlier the Chairperson of Department of Biochemistry in the [[Bose Institute]] in [[Kolkata]]. She was Chairperson of an Indo-British Wellcome Trust/ DBT India Alliance, an organization to promote medical research in India.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://indiabioscience.org/columns/conversations/ten-women-ten-questions-anuradha-lohia | title=Ten women, ten questions: Anuradha Lohia | publisher=indiabioscience.org | date=17 July 2015 | accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Education and career==\nShe was a student of Modern High School for Girls in [[Calcutta]]. She did a B.Sc. in Physiology from [[Presidency College, Kolkata|Presidency College]] in [[Calcutta University]] and M.Sc. in Physiology from [[Rajabazar Science College]], [[Calcutta University]] and later did her doctorate in [[Vibrio cholerae]] from the [[Indian Institute of Chemical Biology]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Anuradha Lohia,|url=http://www.streeshakti.com/Anuradha-Lohia.aspx|publisher=StreeShakti|accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref> She was visiting scientist in various universities in the World. She did her Postdoctoral research in New York University Medical Centre. She was elected a fellow of the [[Indian Academy of Sciences]]. She was also awarded the Stree Shakti award and the UNESCO Molecular and Cell Biology network grant.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-aca}}\n{{s-bef|before = [[Malabika Sarkar]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title = [[Presidency University, Kolkata|Vice-Chancellor of Presidency University, Kolkata]]|years = since 2014}}\n{{s-aft|after= incumbent}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lohia, Anuradha}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Indian parasitologists]]\n[[Category:Indian women biologists]]